</p></sec><sec id="Sec12"><title>Baseline biochemical parameters</title><p>Serum Na concentration on admission was significantly lower in the intervention arm (120.7&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;5.5&#x02009;mmol/l) in comparison with the control arm (124.1&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;3.1&#x02009;mmol/l) with a <italic>P</italic> value of 0.017. All other biochemical parameters, apart from serum osmolality, did not differ between two groups, as shown in Table&#x000a0;<xref rid="Tab2" ref-type="table">2</xref>.<table-wrap id="Tab2"><label>Table 2</label><caption><p>Baseline biochemical parameters in both study arms</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><thead><tr><th>Biochemical parameters</th><th>Control group <italic>N</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;23</th><th>Intervention group <italic>N</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;18</th><th>
