</p></sec><sec id="Sec13"><title>Endocrine input</title><p>All patients (100&#x02009;%) in the intervention group received endocrine input compared with 12/23 patients (52.2&#x02009;%) in the control group (<italic>P</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;0.001). The mean time interval between admission and expert input in the intensive arm was 1.8 days, much shorter than in the &#x02018;routine&#x02019; care arm (5.7 days; <italic>P</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;0.007).</p></sec><sec id="Sec14"><title>Treatment of SIAD</title><p>In the group receiving &#x02018;routine&#x02019; clinical care, 26.1&#x02009;% of patients had no specific treatment for SIAD vs. no untreated cases in the intervention group (<italic>P</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;0.027). The mean number of therapeutic modalities used in the control arm was 1.2, significantly lower than in the intervention arm (1.9; <italic>P</italic>&#x02009;=&#x02009;0.041). The frequency of utilisation of different therapeutic modalities is illustrated in Table&#x000a0;<xref rid="Tab3" ref-type="table">3</xref>.<table-wrap id="Tab3"><label>Table 3</label><caption><p>Frequency of utilisation of different therapeutic modalities</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><thead><tr><th>Treatment modality</th><th>Control group</th><th>Intervention group</th><th>
